# Cursor Rules for Markdown Mermaid Viewer

## MANDATORY: Read MASTER.md First
Before generating any code, you MUST read and understand `docs/MASTER.md`.

## Project Context
This is the **Markdown Mermaid Viewer** VS Code extension project. It provides a refined Mermaid preview in Markdown and strong support for Kindle/EPUB/PDF export. Development follows AI Spec Driven Development (docs structure from ai-spec-driven-development).

## Key Constraints from MASTER.md
- **TypeScript**: strict mode, no `any` (use `unknown` or proper types)
- **No magic numbers**: use named constants or config; document units and ranges
- **No console.log in production**: use VS Code OutputChannel
- **Error handling**: do not swallow errors; surface to user or log
- **Functions**: single responsibility, ~30 lines target
- **Naming**: camelCase (variables), UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (constants), PascalCase (types/interfaces)

